To prove the pumping lemma for context-free languages, we need to show that for any context-free language $L$, there exists a natural number $n$ such that for any string $z \in L$ with $|z| \geq n$, there exist strings $u, v, w, x, y$ such that $z = uvwxy$, $|v| \geq 1$, $|vw| \leq n$, and for all $k \geq 0$, the string $uv^kwx^ky \in L$.

